==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Indistinctness
<hw>In`dis*tinct"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or condition
of being indistinct; lack of definiteness; dimness; confusion; <as>as,
the <ex>indistinctness</ex> of a picture, or of comprehension;
<ex>indistinctness</ex> of vision.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>indistinguishability</ent>⟦br⟧
